WEBVTT

00:00:00.399 --> 00:00:03.439
hello everyone this is mr p on today's

00:00:03.439 --> 00:00:05.600
lesson we're going to take a look at

00:00:05.600 --> 00:00:09.519
the structure of a short story

00:00:09.519 --> 00:00:12.400
so let's get started what is a short

00:00:12.400 --> 00:00:14.320
story

00:00:14.320 --> 00:00:17.199
and what are the elements it is a brief

00:00:17.199 --> 00:00:19.279
narrative containing characters

00:00:19.279 --> 00:00:22.560
a simple plot and a conflict which leads

00:00:22.560 --> 00:00:27.199
to a climax and a swift conclusion

00:00:27.199 --> 00:00:31.439
the five elements are characters

00:00:31.439 --> 00:00:35.360
setting conflict theme

00:00:35.360 --> 00:00:38.000
and plot

00:00:38.480 --> 00:00:42.399
let's take a look at characters first

00:00:42.399 --> 00:00:45.760
people animal things that are involved

00:00:45.760 --> 00:00:47.720
in the plot of the story

00:00:47.720 --> 00:00:48.960
[Music]

00:00:48.960 --> 00:00:51.760
there can be talking animals fantasy

00:00:51.760 --> 00:00:53.039
characters

00:00:53.039 --> 00:00:56.800
etc the protagonist

00:00:56.800 --> 00:00:59.600
is the main character it is usually the

00:00:59.600 --> 00:00:59.920
good

00:00:59.920 --> 00:01:03.440
guy the antagonist instead

00:01:03.440 --> 00:01:07.200
creates conflict for the main character

00:01:07.200 --> 00:01:10.400
it is usually the bad guy

00:01:10.400 --> 00:01:14.159
here we have nemo imo is a protagonist

00:01:14.159 --> 00:01:17.680
or cinderella also is a protagonist

00:01:17.680 --> 00:01:20.720
but we have the joker the joker

00:01:20.720 --> 00:01:23.439
was the antagonist and recently we have

00:01:23.439 --> 00:01:24.159
seen him

00:01:24.159 --> 00:01:27.960
as a protagonist of a movie

00:01:27.960 --> 00:01:29.600
[Music]

00:01:29.600 --> 00:01:33.040
so the setting is the time the time of

00:01:33.040 --> 00:01:33.600
day

00:01:33.600 --> 00:01:37.360
the season present past future

00:01:37.360 --> 00:01:40.720
the location the country the planet

00:01:40.720 --> 00:01:44.320
the town the buildings it helps create

00:01:44.320 --> 00:01:44.880
the mood

00:01:44.880 --> 00:01:48.560
and atmosphere of the story

00:01:52.840 --> 00:01:54.960
conflict the main problem the

00:01:54.960 --> 00:01:56.000
protagonist

00:01:56.000 --> 00:01:59.520
is trying to solve something troubling

00:01:59.520 --> 00:02:00.399
or bad

00:02:00.399 --> 00:02:04.079
that has happened in the story conflicts

00:02:04.079 --> 00:02:05.360
are usually resolved

00:02:05.360 --> 00:02:10.080
at the end of the story zap

00:02:10.479 --> 00:02:14.400
types of conflict man versus men

00:02:14.400 --> 00:02:16.959
here pay attention because it is written

00:02:16.959 --> 00:02:17.440
men

00:02:17.440 --> 00:02:20.800
but it can be also woman versus woman

00:02:20.800 --> 00:02:23.280
we have fewer examples like batman

00:02:23.280 --> 00:02:24.000
against

00:02:24.000 --> 00:02:27.040
the joker for example superman against

00:02:27.040 --> 00:02:29.840
the antagonist

00:02:30.080 --> 00:02:33.280
man versus nature again here can be

00:02:33.280 --> 00:02:36.879
woman versus nature example

00:02:36.879 --> 00:02:40.640
titanic so titanic hit an iceberg

00:02:40.640 --> 00:02:44.560
so we have men versus nature

00:02:44.560 --> 00:02:48.959
tornado the movie tornado

00:02:48.959 --> 00:02:52.239
man versus himself for example in the

00:02:52.239 --> 00:02:52.959
joker

00:02:52.959 --> 00:02:56.560
he fights against himself to find a

00:02:56.560 --> 00:02:58.319
solution to his problem

00:02:58.319 --> 00:03:02.080
or the lion king for example

00:03:02.080 --> 00:03:05.360
man versus society so again here we have

00:03:05.360 --> 00:03:06.319
the joker

00:03:06.319 --> 00:03:09.280
so as you can see there can be many

00:03:09.280 --> 00:03:11.920
types of conflict in one story

00:03:11.920 --> 00:03:15.920
or robin hood also man versus society

00:03:15.920 --> 00:03:19.280
and here i wrote there can be many

00:03:19.280 --> 00:03:23.440
types of conflict in a story

00:03:23.519 --> 00:03:26.879
theme what the author wants you to learn

00:03:26.879 --> 00:03:31.360
or know a broad idea about life

00:03:31.360 --> 00:03:34.720
usually not stated it must be guessed

00:03:34.720 --> 00:03:37.760
examples be good to everyone do not be

00:03:37.760 --> 00:03:39.120
greedy

00:03:39.120 --> 00:03:43.280
power corrupts love takes faith

00:03:43.280 --> 00:03:47.280
etc now let's take a look at the plot

00:03:47.280 --> 00:03:50.640
the plot consists of five parts

00:03:50.640 --> 00:03:53.439
introduction or exposition is the

00:03:53.439 --> 00:03:54.239
setting

00:03:54.239 --> 00:03:57.439
the background and the characters

00:03:57.439 --> 00:04:00.640
the rising action is the conflict where

00:04:00.640 --> 00:04:04.000
suspense is created the climax

00:04:04.000 --> 00:04:06.720
is the highest point of the story the

00:04:06.720 --> 00:04:08.319
deciding factor

00:04:08.319 --> 00:04:10.799
in the falling action the protagonist

00:04:10.799 --> 00:04:11.599
completes

00:04:11.599 --> 00:04:14.879
the action then the resolution is the

00:04:14.879 --> 00:04:15.760
final end

00:04:15.760 --> 00:04:19.440
the solution of the story so how does

00:04:19.440 --> 00:04:21.519
the blood diagram look like

00:04:21.519 --> 00:04:24.000
well it looks like a mountain we have

00:04:24.000 --> 00:04:26.080
the exposition at the beginning

00:04:26.080 --> 00:04:29.440
then the rising action then the climax

00:04:29.440 --> 00:04:31.919
you reach the top then the falling

00:04:31.919 --> 00:04:33.120
action

00:04:33.120 --> 00:04:35.360
and the resolution is the end of the

00:04:35.360 --> 00:04:37.759
story

00:04:38.800 --> 00:04:42.160
so introduction or exposition this is

00:04:42.160 --> 00:04:44.560
where you must introduce the setting

00:04:44.560 --> 00:04:47.680
so when and where the background

00:04:47.680 --> 00:04:50.080
a set of events created for the plot

00:04:50.080 --> 00:04:53.360
preceding and leading up to the plot

00:04:53.360 --> 00:04:55.440
the characters the protagonist or

00:04:55.440 --> 00:04:56.639
protagonists

00:04:56.639 --> 00:04:59.759
antagonists or antagonists

00:04:59.759 --> 00:05:04.720
is a choice so racing action

00:05:04.720 --> 00:05:07.919
it is a series of significant incidents

00:05:07.919 --> 00:05:10.960
that produce suspense interest

00:05:10.960 --> 00:05:14.639
and tension in a narrative in literary

00:05:14.639 --> 00:05:15.759
works

00:05:15.759 --> 00:05:19.360
a rising action includes all decisions

00:05:19.360 --> 00:05:21.759
characters flaws and background

00:05:21.759 --> 00:05:23.600
situations that together

00:05:23.600 --> 00:05:26.800
create turns and twists which in turn

00:05:26.800 --> 00:05:30.400
lead to a climax

00:05:30.479 --> 00:05:33.919
so the climax it is often identified

00:05:33.919 --> 00:05:37.199
as the highest point of interest in a

00:05:37.199 --> 00:05:38.720
story

00:05:38.720 --> 00:05:40.880
at this point the conflict is at the

00:05:40.880 --> 00:05:42.960
highest point of tension

00:05:42.960 --> 00:05:45.199
then we have the falling action it

00:05:45.199 --> 00:05:47.120
happens right after the climax

00:05:47.120 --> 00:05:49.360
when the main problem of the story is

00:05:49.360 --> 00:05:50.960
resolved

00:05:50.960 --> 00:05:53.600
the falling action ends the short story

00:05:53.600 --> 00:05:54.479
resolves

00:05:54.479 --> 00:05:56.880
the unanswered situations and leads

00:05:56.880 --> 00:05:59.840
toward the closure

00:06:00.319 --> 00:06:03.360
and finally we have the resolution

00:06:03.360 --> 00:06:08.560
it is where the main problem is resolved

00:06:08.720 --> 00:06:11.039
the resolution occurs after the falling

00:06:11.039 --> 00:06:12.960
action and is typically

00:06:12.960 --> 00:06:16.080
where the story ends well

